  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get into the Australian National University?",
  "response": "Getting into the Australian National University (ANU) involves several steps, depending on whether you are an undergraduate or a postgraduate applicant. Here are some general guidelines for both:\n\n### For Undergraduate Admission:\n\n1. **Meet Academic Requirements**:\n   - You need a high school qualification equivalent to the Australian Year 12. This usually involves completing the International Baccalaureate (IB) or A Levels.\n   - Check specific course prerequisites as some programs may have specific subject requirements.\n\n2. **Admission Score**:\n   - Your admission will generally be based on your ATAR (Australian Tertiary Admission Rank) or its equivalent for international students. \n   - ANU publishes the minimum ATAR scores for various courses annually.\n\n3. **English Language Proficiency**:\n   - If English is not your first language, you may need to demonstrate English language proficiency through standardized tests like IELTS, TOEFL, or others.\n\n4. **Apply**:\n   - Applications for undergraduate programs are typically submitted through the Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) for domestic students. International applicants can apply directly through the ANU website.\n\n5. **Personal Statement and Portfolio**:\n   - Some programs may require a personal statement or a portfolio of work.\n\n6. **Interviews**:\n   - Certain courses may require an interview or additional assessments.\n\n### For Postgraduate Admission:\n\n1. **Meet Academic Requirements**:\n   - You need a relevant undergraduate degree from a recognized institution. Each program may have specific entry requirements.\n\n2. **English Language Proficiency**:\n   - Similar to undergraduate requirements, you may need to provide proof of English proficiency.\n\n3. **Experience and Background**:\n   - Some postgraduate courses may consider your professional experience, especially for programs like an MBA.\n\n4. **Application Process**:\n   - You can apply directly through the ANU website. Prepare your academic transcripts and any necessary documentation.\n\n5. **Supporting Documents**:\n   - This may include a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and a CV.\n\n### Additional Considerations:\n\n- **Open Days and Information Sessions**: Attend open days or information sessions to learn more about your desired program and the application process.\n- **Financial Aid and Scholarships**: Explore scholarship options that might be available for both domestic and international students.\n- **Important Deadlines**: Be aware of application deadlines, which can vary by program and whether you are applying as a domestic or international student.\n\nRemember to check the ANU official website for the most accurate and detailed information, including specific requirements for courses that interest you.",
